Female . Body shape and colouration as in the other representatives of the Subggroup 2 (
Kaya et al. 2012
), mostly resembling P. t urc i c u s . Ovipositor long for the group ( 9.2–10.1 mm ), similar in length to the taxa of Subgroups 1 and 2 (l.c.). The lamellae (lateral processes of the base of the lower ovipositor valve) are short and laterally expanded with obtuse triangular lateral corners; the pit formed between lamellae and gonangulum is shallow, moderately wide.
